com.polarion.alm.tracker

Interface IBaselinesManager


  • public interface IBaselinesManager
    Functionality related to baselines. Each instance of IBaselinesManager is bound to particular project, therefore the methods lack the project parameter.
    Author:
    dobisekm
    See Also:
    ITrackerProject.getBaselinesManager()

      • getBaselines

        IPObjectList getBaselines()
        Convenience method, can be done by querying.
        Returns:
        The list of baselines defined in given project. Never returns null, might return empty list.

      • getRevisionBaseline

        IBaseline getRevisionBaseline(java.lang.String revision)
        Convenience method.
        Returns:
        Returns the baseline, which correspond to the given revision. Returns null if the revision is not baselined.

      • scheduleComparisonJob

        IJob scheduleComparisonJob(java.lang.String r1,
                           java.lang.String r2,
                           IUser author)
        Schedules the comparison job. Only on ejob can run at a time, therefore the new job might be started in waiting state. After the job is successfully finished, then it's result will appear in the Reports listing. If it fials, then no result will be produced (the appropriate jobs API can then be used by users to evaluate the results).
        Parameters:
        r1 -
        r2 -
        author -
        Returns:
        instance of the scheduled job.

      • getCurrentJobStatus

        java.lang.String getCurrentJobStatus()
        Returns:
        Either user-friendly job status message (multiple lines of text - a log) or null if no job is currently running in given project, of if the job is still waiting.

      • isJobRunning

        boolean isJobRunning()
        Determines if ther is a comparison job active for this project.
        Returns:
        true, if there is at least one comparison job running or waiting for this project, false otherwise.

      • listExistingReports

        IComparisonReport[] listExistingReports()
        Returns existing comparison reports.
        Returns:
        An array containin existing reports, starting by newest, going to oldest.
